channel.title: What the hell
channel.description:
Just for some reason I cannot remember the way isincoords go, like this
[code](coordX >= 2708) && (coordX <= 2815) && (coordY <= 3227) && (coordY >= 3145)[/code]
I thought coord x1 is northwest X and coord y1 was northwest y then coord x2 was southeast X and coord y2 was southeast y

item.title: What the hell
item.dc:creator: @deathschaos9 DeathsChaos9
item.description:
@deathschaos9 wrote:

For sake of argument lets say your current X and Y coords are 2800 and 3200.

If coordX is greater than or equal to 2708.

If coordX is less than or equal to 2815.

If coordY is greater than or equal to 3145.

If coordX is less than or equal to 3227.

Everything seems to be in check
